.NET is an open source developer platform, created by Microsoft, for building
many different types of applications. It provides a standard set of base class
libraries and APIs that are common to all .NET applications. .NET apps can be
written in such languages as C#, F#, or Visual Basic.

Using LibreSSL is not supported. Enabling the LIBRESSL port option will patch
the sources, so building with LibreSSL works, but this will just disable some
functionality and also interfere with runtime detection of OpenSSL APIs. .NET
projects built with this option set might fail to work correctly and are likely
to fail on machines using OpenSSL.
